EvaTRiP (Evaluation Tools for River environmental Planning) are developed by Aqua Restoration Research Center in PWRI(National Research and Development Agency Public Works Research Institute),Masahiko Sekine Dr.Eng. Professor of Yamaguchi University, Norio Tanaka Dr.Eng. Professor of Saitama University and Junji Yagisawa Dr.Eng Associate Professor of Saitama University. The purpose of development is to use it of the examination of the plan about the stability of the river channel, river environment and the maintenance in the small and medium size river.

This tools can evaluate followings
- the necessity of river bank protection
- the region of critical grain size
- the region of terrestrial plant grows
- the region of fish habitat
So you can use it for river environment research and river planning.
